main event: On May 11, 1954, at Keesler Air Force Base in Biloxi, Mississippi, there was a sighting of 7 to 9 round, pale orange objects flying in a V formation. The observation lasted approximately 2 seconds as the objects flew in an arc from a 45-degree slew at 200 degrees to a point overhead. There was also the sound of a low pitched flutter and a diffused configuration at the rear of the objects.
interesting points: The observation involved 7 to 9 round, pale orange objects flying in a V formation, which is a highly unusual sighting.
The objects were observed to have a diffused configuration at the rear and emitted a sound of low pitched flutter, adding to the mysterious nature of the sighting.
The sighting was noted as a 'Solid observation,' indicating that the witnesses found the event to be significant and credible.
Analysis of the factors and interrogation of the observer did not result in an explanation of the sighting, leaving it unexplained.
The observation was conducted in compliance with specific Air Force regulations, emphasizing the official nature of the report.
sighted object: 7-9 round, pale orange objects flying in a V formation
location: Keesler Air Force Base, Biloxi, Mississippi
